(98, 1, '2018-11-09 09:28:45', '2018-11-09 09:28:45', '<p class=\"western\">Announcement of the concert came out in a press conference, held at the Robi Corporate Office in the capital on Wednesday, where the<i>LRB</i> frontman Ayub Bachchu revealed the band\'s plan to celebrate it\'s 25th anniversary. Other band members including Swapan on bass, Masud on guitar, Romel on drums, and the band manager Shamim, were present there as well.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Robi Yonder Music, who supported the event, made a special offer for it\'s users to get the concert entry ticket out of charge. To get free entry tickets, any Robi Yonder Music user have to listen to at least five songs under “LRB Turns Twenty Five” playlist while 200 listeners will be awarded with two free tickets each.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Wizard Showbiz, an event management outfit will be organising the concert who earlier organised the the Band\'s 12th years anniversary concert.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Formed in 1991, the band, shortened from Love Runs Blind, released their first double album <i>L.R.B 1</i> and <i>L.R.B 2</i> just a year later, and has released 11 studio albums till date. Their latest album <i>Juddho</i> came out in 2012.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Besides, they have one live album, two compilations, and numerous mixed albums. LRB is the country\'s only band to have the credit of releasing two double albums, among which one was their debut.</p>', 'LRB\'s silver jubilee', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lrbs-silver-jubilee', '', '', '2018-11-09 09:28:45', '2018-11-09 09:28:45', '', 0, 'http://localhost/fund/?p=98', 0, 'post', '', 0),
